KUWAIT CITY, Nov. 15 (Xinhua) -- Kuwait is committed to the unity and stability of Yemen and restoring its security and safety, Kuwait's Foreign Minister Sheikh Ahmad Nasser Al-Mohammad Al-Sabah said on Monday. The minister made the remarks during a meeting with visiting UN Special Envoy for Yemen Hans Grundberg. He also stressed his country's support for the international efforts, Saudi Arabia's peace initiative in Yemen, and relevant UN Security Council resolutions to end the crisis in Yemen and tackle the deteriorating humanitarian situation. For his part, Hans Grundberg praised Kuwait's efforts in supporting the Yemeni people and its contribution towards achieving security and stability on the Yemeni lands while trying to ease the suffering of the Yemeni people. Enditem